    {
      "id": "jag-MeJiRP7LaWHi6pIoc",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -622.0372690113485,
      "y": 4186.178018330653,
      "width": 684.95947265625,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b50",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1357860680,
      "version": 601,
      "versionNonce": 743779912,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768237194488,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Alert Manager Cluster ( silencing, inhibition, grouping, rate\nlimiting/throttling(repeat_interval), cooldown(group_interval), Receiver\nintegration(slack/email/pager ), and in memory queue)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "pLXRbbfkeJhgkrvCpo3CE",
      "originalText": "Alert Manager Cluster ( silencing, inhibition, grouping, rate limiting/throttling(repeat_interval), cooldown(group_interval), Receiver integration(slack/email/pager ), and in memory queue)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "WsiHOATHhPNY3VuPVNQkG",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1432.8533237004963,
      "y": 3919.2524607595797,
      "width": 460.79358527594167,
      "height": 439.55777714901336,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b51",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1549794360,
      "version": 2391,
      "versionNonce": 951457864,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768236534794,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Note: Multi region alerts will be idempotent as\nevery alert will have the region cluster_id and\nregion. We will direct Thanos Alerting Rules to a\nThanos Query that is regional. If the user\nwants to have alerts that are based on\nbusiness logic and regional/cluster uniqueness is\nnot valid we would build a central alert manager\ncluster service but extract those two labels in\nthe Alert Manager configuration. The user\nwould then create alerting rules on a global\nThanos Alerting Rules framework that direct to\nthe global Alert Manager. This should not be\nthe norm. 99% of alerts should be based on\nregional logic. The global workflow would have\nless availability, more cost, and be slower than\nthe regional instances. However, this would be\nthe same framework the SRE team could use\nfor global alerting across different namespaces. ",
      "fontSize": 19.535901206622817,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Note: Multi region alerts will be idempotent as every alert will have the region cluster_id and region. We will direct Thanos Alerting Rules to a Thanos Query that is regional. If the user wants to have alerts that are based on business logic and regional/cluster uniqueness is not valid we would build a central alert manager cluster service but extract those two labels in the Alert Manager configuration. The user would then create alerting rules on a global Thanos Alerting Rules framework that direct to the global Alert Manager. This should not be the norm. 99% of alerts should be based on regional logic. The global workflow would have less availability, more cost, and be slower than the regional instances. However, this would be the same framework the SRE team could use for global alerting across different namespaces. ",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
